==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meloe
<hw>Mel"o*e</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[ NL., fr. Gr. <?/ to probe a
wound.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of beetles without wings,
but having short oval elytra; the oil beetles. These beetles are
sometimes used instead of cantharides for raising blisters. See
<cref>Oil beetle</cref>, under <er>Oil</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

